The issue with your code is that you are trying to switch to the same window again after clicking the button. Selenium WebDriver does not allow you to switch to the same window twice. To resolve this issue, you can store the window handle of the current window before switching to the new window, and then switch to the new window using the stored window handle.

Here's the modified code:
```java
// Store the window handle of the current window
String winHandleBefore = driver.getWindowHandle();

// Click the button
driver.findElement(By.id("ImageButton5")).click();

// Wait for some time
Thread.sleep(3000);

// Switch to the new window using the stored window handle
driver.switchTo().window(winHandleBefore);

// Enter the text in the new window
driver.findElement(By.id("txtEnterCptCode")).sendKeys("99219");
```
Note that you should also ensure that the new window is opened before trying to switch to it. If the new window is not opened before switching, Selenium WebDriver will throw a `NoSuchWindowException`.
